  "text": "Different types of content-based image queries have been suggested and analyzed: example images; rough, blurry drawings of the desired colors; simple outline sketches; and combinations or extensions thereof [CITATION_1] . We believe that outline sketches are typically easier and faster to generate than a complete color description of the scene. And they can be generated for arbitrary desired images, while example images may or may not be at hand when searching. In addition, input devices change in favor of sketching as touch-enabled devices become more common. In other words, sketch-based image retrieval (SBIR) is a relevant means of querying large image databases.",
